---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import FinalCta from '../components/FinalCta.astro';
const title = "Careers | Wright Construction Management";
const description = "Join a small, owner-minded construction management team. We look for field-tested, detail-obsessed professionals who put their name on the outcome.";
---
<Base title={title} description={description}>
  <section class="page-banner"><div class="wrap">
    <div class="breadcrumb"><a href="/">Home</a> / Careers</div>
    <h1>Careers</h1>
    <p>We build a small bench of people who take ownership seriously. If you'd rather run the messy middle of a real project than push paper from a corner office, we should talk.</p>
  </div></section>
  <section><div class="wrap">
    <span class="eyebrow">Who we want to work with</span><h2 class="section-title">Field-tested, detail-obsessed, owner-minded.</h2>
    <p class="lead" style="margin-top:16px">We look for construction and project-management professionals who think in terms of the owner's outcome&mdash;schedule certainty, cost visibility, and fewer surprises&mdash;not just the next task. People who are comfortable in an active plant, around inspectors and equipment vendors, and who close out a job as carefully as they start it.</p>
    <div class="values-grid">
      <div class="value"><div class="n">01</div><h3>Ownership</h3><p>You treat the schedule and the budget like they're yours. No finger-pointing, no hand-offs that drop the ball.</p></div>
      <div class="value"><div class="n">02</div><h3>Expose Risk Early</h3><p>You'd rather have the hard conversation in preconstruction than the expensive one in the field.</p></div>
      <div class="value"><div class="n">03</div><h3>Practical Leadership</h3><p>You coordinate designers, trades, inspectors, and operators without drama&mdash;and keep production running.</p></div>
      <div class="value"><div class="n">04</div><h3>Detail Discipline</h3><p>Scope gaps and communication breakdowns are where projects fail. You close them before they open.</p></div>
      <div class="value"><div class="n">05</div><h3>Accountability</h3><p>You say what you'll do, then do it&mdash;and you put your name on the closeout.</p></div>
      <div class="value"><div class="n">06</div><h3>Build Better</h3><p>You care about the craft and the client. Good enough isn't.</p></div>
    </div>
    <div class="empty-state">
      <h3>No open roles right now&mdash;but we're always meeting good people.</h3>
      <p>We hire deliberately and keep our team small so every project gets senior attention. If you're an estimator, project manager, superintendent, or preconstruction lead who fits the above, introduce yourself and we'll keep you in mind as projects come on.</p>
      <a href="mailto:jwright@wrightcm.co?subject=Careers%20Inquiry" class="btn btn-primary">Email Us About Future Roles</a>
    </div>
  </div></section>
  <FinalCta heading="Know someone who'd be a fit?" sub="We grow through relationships and referrals. Send an introduction to jwright@wrightcm.co and we'll take it from there." label="Get in Touch" />
</Base>
